cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories as it deals with adversarial attacks on deep neural networks. It may also belong to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category as it discusses the vulnerability of deep neural networks to attacks. Additionally, it could be classified under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories as it proposes a new objective function and extends previous works on black box adversarial attacks using evolution strategies and other derivative-free optimization methods.
